name: LUMBUNGASRI | Puri Lumbung Restaurants, Cottage & Waterpark
address: Jl. Puri Lumbung, Penarungan, Kec. Mengwi, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80352, Indonesia
review 1:
I came here for their gurami rica-rica, which I found through Google Maps, and it was quite far from where I was staying. With a 4++ rating on Google Maps, I decided to give it a try. After a 30-minute journey, I arrived at the restaurant, which was very secluded. I couldn't find any staff at first, but I eventually found someone who told me they were on a break.

Once everything seemed normal, I found the staff to be friendly and always smiling. I ordered the gurami rica-rica, which came with rice, and like any other Indonesian, I ordered iced tea. I waited for about 20 minutes, enjoying the natural surroundings before my food arrived. However, the gurami was not as spicy as I expected it to be.

Overall, I loved the ambiance of the place, but it's not ideal for solo travelers. I recommend bringing family or friends to fill up the large tables.
review 2: The place is quite good, the bathroom is very clean, the service is also good.  Anyone can come here.  There are games like slide.  The entry ticket price is only 10k and it can be cheaper if ordered through the traveloka apps.  Suggestion for those who don't like swimming in crowded places: come to this place on weekdays at 2pm.
review 3:
A nice place to go. Touristic in all sensible way. It's like a fusion of nature with commercial service.

Not over priced. Lots of staff everywhere.

Many photo opportunity. The waterfall! Is spectacular.

All with all. Yes go there.
20k entrance, including a stempel!

Tot chilling out, halfway up/down. Nice place to relax. For that reason alone. I come back.
review 4: Location is good and food taste is mediocre. Ordered chicken rice bowl, fried noodles, fried rice, etc. Fried noodles and rice were oily and rice bowl portion is lacking. Parking lot is spacious and menu selection is decent. Service time is sub par and the restaurant is clearly understaffed.
review 5:
Every weekend this place is soooo busy, will be better on weekdays. We visit almost once in 2 months.
Last weekend, this place was not in its best condition. Water cleanliness bad, we ordered nasi goreng, but came up with half normal portion. The rest was so so.

name: Warung Laksmi Penarungan

review 1:

Very quiet at night , really relaxing and peacefull
review 2: The food is delicious and reasonably priced
review 3: Set amidst padifields. Slow service and food is so-so only. Pricey for the place it's in.
review 4: Very nice staff, good food, reasonable prices :)
